<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="173" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1869,2002]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1869,1894]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head short, narrower than trunk; foot long, 
<number box="[782,826,1870,1894]" pageId="22" pageNumber="173" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2−3</number>
pseudosegments; toes conical, with offset distal half; corona slightly oblique; rami with long obtuse alulae; fulcrum with large basal plate; manubria with large head and incurved cauda; a ribbon composed of two bands of short and long sclerite bodies laterally from dorsally recurved part of rami.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
