<subSubSection lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="175" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1579,2036]" lastBlockId="24.[151,1437,151,717]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="175" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,478,1939,1964]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Description of female.</emphasis>
Body (
<figureCitation box="[577,665,1939,1964]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1493,1515]" captionTargetBox="[202,1393,758,1479]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[193,1402,751,1483]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pleurotrocha fontanetoi sp. nov. A. Female, dorsal; B. eye, female; C. male, dorsal; D. toe, female, lateral; E. toes, female, dorsal; F. trophi, complete set, ventral; G. incus, lateral; H. left malleus, outer view; I. right malleus, outer view. Scale bars: A, C: 50 µm; D − I: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240574/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
Fig. 
<number box="[638,665,1939,1963]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
A) stout fusiform, somewhat gibbous. Head and foot offset by transversal fold. Head short, narrower than trunk, with transversal fold. Corona slightly oblique, with small lateral tufts of cilia. Dorsal antenna near posterior 
<number box="[633,643,2011,2035]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[655,669,2011,2035]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" value="3.0">3</number>
of head. Eyespot on brain, a colourless globule with two minute redpigmented granules (
<figureCitation box="[392,477,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1493,1515]" captionTargetBox="[202,1393,758,1479]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[193,1402,751,1483]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pleurotrocha fontanetoi sp. nov. A. Female, dorsal; B. eye, female; C. male, dorsal; D. toe, female, lateral; E. toes, female, dorsal; F. trophi, complete set, ventral; G. incus, lateral; H. left malleus, outer view; I. right malleus, outer view. Scale bars: A, C: 50 µm; D − I: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240574/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">
Fig. 
<number box="[447,477,152,176]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Trunk elongate-ovate with transversal fold in posterior 
<number box="[1159,1170,152,176]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1182,1197,152,176]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" value="3.0">3</number>
. Tail large, rounded. Foot long, cylindrical, 
<number box="[405,447,188,212]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2‒3</number>
pseudosegments, occasionally appearing wrinkled proximally. Toes (
<figureCitation box="[1222,1306,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1493,1515]" captionTargetBox="[202,1393,758,1479]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[193,1402,751,1483]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pleurotrocha fontanetoi sp. nov. A. Female, dorsal; B. eye, female; C. male, dorsal; D. toe, female, lateral; E. toes, female, dorsal; F. trophi, complete set, ventral; G. incus, lateral; H. left malleus, outer view; I. right malleus, outer view. Scale bars: A, C: 50 µm; D − I: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240574/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">
Figs 
<number box="[1278,1306,188,212]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
D, E) short, stout conical, tapering to tubular tips, with more or less distinctly offset distal half. Pedal glands club-shaped with reservoirs at base of toes. Stomach separated from intestine by weak constriction. Gastric glands large, rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">
Trophi (
<figureCitation box="[288,372,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1493,1515]" captionTargetBox="[202,1393,758,1479]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[193,1402,751,1483]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 18. Pleurotrocha fontanetoi sp. nov. A. Female, dorsal; B. eye, female; C. male, dorsal; D. toe, female, lateral; E. toes, female, dorsal; F. trophi, complete set, ventral; G. incus, lateral; H. left malleus, outer view; I. right malleus, outer view. Scale bars: A, C: 50 µm; D − I: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240574/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">
Figs 
<number box="[345,372,296,320]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
F −I, 
<number box="[427,456,296,320]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" value="19.0">19</number>
) asymmetrical, left more strongly developed than right. Rami with large, elongate blunt alulae pointing latero-caudally, and large dorsally recurved apical branch bearing comb of tiny toothlets at inner margin; basal rami part with irregular knob-shaped teeth on inner margins, and strong, left basal apophysis; basal chambers fairly small, left one with large opening. Fulcrum robust, long, plank-shaped and fairly high, ventral margin reinforced, distal end broadly expanded into oblique oval plate. Unci five incompletely connected teeth of decreasing length, first two teeth with head, the others linear; left uncus more strongly developed, its first tooth with distinct head and prominent medial projection at ventral margin; right uncus more slender, head of teeth weak, projection at ventral margin weak; subuncus composed of few irregular knob-like prominences. Manubria with relatively large elongate head and dorsally recurved cauda, left manubrium largest; openings of ventral and medial chamber narrow, elongate, opening of dorsal chamber broad. A broad ribbon (
<figureCitation box="[1042,1128,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1652,1674]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,267,1630]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[151,1436,267,1631]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 19. Pleurotrocha fontanetoi sp. nov., SEM photographs of trophi. A. Complete set, ventral; B. incus, ventral; C. incus, lateral right; D. right uncus, inner view; E. distal part of ribbon of short and long sclerite bodies; F. left manubrium, outer view; G. right manubrium, outer view; H. incus, oblique ventro-caudal; I, J. complete set, oblique ventro-frontal. R: ribbon of sclerite bodies. Scale bars: A − D, F − J: 10 µm; E: 1 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240575/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">
Figs 
<number box="[1100,1128,620,644]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
E, I, J: r) composed of two bands of long (frontal) and short (caudal) sclerite bodies inserted laterally from recurved distal part of rami, and partly covered by malleus.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240574/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" targetBox="[202,1393,758,1479]" targetPageId="24">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1493,1577]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,1493,1515]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">FIGURE 18.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[297,541,1493,1515]" class="Eurotatoria" family="Notommatidae" genus="Pleurotrocha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ploima" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" phylum="Rotifera" rank="species" species="fontanetoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[297,541,1493,1515]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">Pleurotrocha fontanetoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[549,631,1493,1515]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[549,631,1493,1515]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
A. Female, dorsal; B. eye, female; C. male, dorsal; D. toe, female, lateral; E. toes, female, dorsal; F. trophi, complete set, ventral; G. incus, lateral; H. left malleus, outer view; I. right malleus, outer view. Scale bars: A, C: 50 µm; D −I: 10 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,1615,2037]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,438,1615,1640]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">Description of male.</emphasis>
Male more or less similar in habitus to female, with small head, oval trunk, and long foot composed of 
<emphasis box="[301,320,1653,1676]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">c.</emphasis>
<number box="[328,342,1652,1677]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" value="5.0">5</number>
pseudosegments; toes conical with more or less distinctly offset distal part.
</paragraph>
